The matrix equation below represents a system of linear equations:

\begin{equation*}
\begin{pmatrix}
3 & 1 & 0 \\
1 & -2 & 1 \\
0 & 1 & 3 
\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}
x \\ y \\ z
\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}
5 \\ -1 \\ 10
\end{pmatrix}
\end{equation*}

Using the Jacobi iterative method, find the solution for the system of equations accurate to four decimal places, given the initial vector $\vec{x}^{(0)} = [0, 0, 0]^T.$
